<subpara id="RM000000U5B01AX_02" type-id="64" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00002HL00000">
<name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>If there is a defect in the MAF meter or an open or short circuit, the voltage level deviates from the normal operating range. The ECM interprets this deviation as a malfunction in the MAF meter and sets a DTC.</ptxt>
<ptxt>Example:</ptxt>
<ptxt>When the sensor output voltage remains less than 0.2 V, or more than 4.9 V, for more than 3 seconds, the ECM sets a DTC.</ptxt>
<ptxt>If the malfunction is not repaired successfully, a DTC is set 3 seconds after the engine is next started.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
